    • Constructor Detail

      • UnboundedInt

        public UnboundedInt​(String number)
        Initialize an empty sequence with a specified String that will be divided into sections of 3. The sections will then be placed into IntNodes in reverse order.
        Param number:
        the string to be passed in as a large number.
        Postcondition:
        This sequence has taken the String input and placed into IntNodes that will range between 0 and 999.

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public UnboundedInt add​(UnboundedInt addend)
        Adds the current UnboundedInt with a passed in UnboundedInt, and returns a new UnboundedInt with a value of the sum of the two UnboundedInts.
        Param addend:
        The UnboundedInt that will be added with the current UnboundedInt.
        Postcondition:
        A new UnboundedInt object that will store the value of the sum of the two UnboundedInts that were added together.

      • multiply

        public UnboundedInt multiply​(UnboundedInt factor)
        Multiplies the current UnboundedInt with a passed in UnboundedInt, and returns a new UnboundedInt with a value of the product of the two UnboundedInts.
        Param addend:
        The UnboundedInt that will be multiplied with the current UnboundedInt.
        Postcondition:
        A new UnboundedInt object that will store the value of the product of the two UnboundedInts that were multiplied together.

        Param - none

      • advance

        public void advance()
        Move forward, so that the cursor element is now the next element in this sequence.
        Param - none
        Postcondition:
